name: Scottie Scheffler
summary: Scottie Scheffler has claimed his second Masters Tournament victory, dominating the competition with an emphatic performance. Despite being separated from his wife, who is pregnant with their child, Scheffler remained focused and determined to succeed. Throughout the tournament, he stated his commitment to leaving the event at a moment's notice if his wife went into labor. Despite his personal circumstances, Scheffler's exceptional talent and unwavering spirit propelled him to victory, earning him his second green jacket. His triumph underscores his ability to balance personal responsibilities with competitive excellence, highlighting the unique challenges faced by athletes with families.

name: Salman Rushdie
summary: Salman Rushdie, the renowned author who survived a near-fatal stabbing in 2022, has released a new memoir titled "Knife." In an interview with The New York Times, Rushdie discusses the writing process and his thoughts on censorship in America today. Critics have hailed the memoir as horrific and upsetting, yet a masterpiece. Rushdie has also appeared on CBS News, where he detailed the moment he was stabbed, stating that a doctor deemed him "lucky" to have survived. Despite the attack, Rushdie remains undeterred and recently attended a book party hosted by Air Mail. His new book explores the threats to free speech from both the left and right, and reflects on the aftermath of his stabbing. Rushdie has since read excerpts from "Knife" on CBS News.

name: Liverpool vs Crystal Palace
summary: Liverpool's Premier League title hopes suffered a setback as they were upset 1-0 at home by Crystal Palace. The result leaves the Reds seven points behind leaders Manchester City with eight games remaining. Odsonne Edouard scored the only goal of the game in the second half. The loss is a major blow to Liverpool's hopes of winning the league for the second time in three seasons. They now need to win all of their remaining games and hope that City drop points in order to have any chance of catching them.
